---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by pierrre at 2015-01-09T15:58:36Z

Why
```php
end($this->rows);
$rowKey = key($this->rows);
reset($this->rows);
```
instead of
```php
$rowKey = count($this->rows) - 1;
```
?

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by boekkooi at 2015-01-09T16:02:01Z

@pierrre because of the way TableHelper->setRow is implemented.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by pierrre at 2015-01-09T16:12:14Z

What are the expected values of `$column` in `setRow()`?
Integer?
An integer lower than `count($this->rows)`?
A string?

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by boekkooi at 2015-01-09T16:24:36Z

@pierrre setRow allows for that. So to avoid BC breaks it's better not to use `count` and use `end`.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by pierrre at 2015-01-09T16:28:04Z

OK I understand.
Thank you.

